"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035120","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-01-10","<p>The Department’s consultation, “Implementing reforms to the leasehold system”, set out how the Government intends to tackle excessive and unjustifiable practices in the leasehold system. We are currently analysing responses and plan to publish the Government’s response in due course.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-01-10T15:09:59.753Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035120/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035120/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035120/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-01-04","Leasehold: Reform","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, when his Department plans to publish the results of the consultation into Implementing reforms to the leasehold system.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","205164"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035121","Ministry of Housing, Communities and Local Government","false","2019-01-09","<p>We are working with the Law Commission to make it easier, faster, fairer and cheaper for leaseholders to buy their freehold or extend their lease. The Law Commission have recently consulted on possible measures, including introducing a prescribed formula that provides fair compensation to the landlord, whilst also helping leaseholders avoid incurring additional court costs. This consultation closed on 7 January 2019 and the Law Commission will be providing recommendations to Government later this year.</p>","South Derbyshire","Mrs Heather Wheeler",,"2019-01-09T17:48:13.347Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035121/answer","Biography information for Mrs Heather Wheeler","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035121/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035121/answer",,,,,"7","Housing, Communities and Local Government","Housing, Communities and Local Government","2019-01-04","Leasehold","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Housing, Communities and Local Government, whether he has made an assessment of the potential merits of bringing forward proposals to protect existing homeowners who are prevented from selling their properties due to the amount of time left on the lease.","false","Biography information for Steve McCabe","Birmingham, Selly Oak","Steve McCabe","205165"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035122","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2019-01-08","<p>The Political Parties, Elections and Referendums Act 2000 requires registered political parties to report cash and non-cash donations and borrowing to the Electoral Commission on a quarterly basis. Parliament made it an offence to deliver, without reasonable excuse, donation reports that are inaccurate or miss the statutory deadline. Parliament also gave the Commission investigation and sanction powers for these, and other, offences. The Commission investigates and where appropriate sanctions inaccurate or late donation reports in line with its Enforcement Policy.</p>","Houghton and Sunderland South","Bridget Phillipson",,"2019-01-08T09:52:54.413Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035122/answer","Biography information for Bridget Phillipson","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035122/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035122/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2019-01-04","Political Parties: Disclosure of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for Houghton and Sunderland South, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, what assessment the Electoral Commission has made of the appropriateness of the Commission's use of civil sanctions for the late submission of political parties' quarterly reports.","false","Biography information for Luke Hall","Thornbury and Yate","Luke Hall","205307"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035123","Home Office","false","2019-01-09","<p>On 19 December, the Government set out its proposals for future skills-based immigration system. Paragraph 6.13 of the White Paper indicates that the Government accepts the Migration Advisory Committee’s recommendation that the skilled migration route in the future system, which will encompass veterinary surgeons, should not be subject to a cap.</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2019-01-09T16:15:44.563Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035123/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035123/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035123/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2019-01-04","Migrant Workers: Veterinary Medicine","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, if he will include veterinary surgeons in his Department's proposals to remove the cap on the number of non-UK skilled workers.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","205157"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035124","Leader of the House","false","2019-01-09","<p>I continue to have regular discussions with Cabinet colleagues on the allocation of time for business and announce the upcoming business at the weekly Business Questions on a Thursday morning.</p>","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom",,"2019-01-09T09:10:19.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035124/answer","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035124/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035124/answer",,,,,"34","Leader of the House","Leader of the House","2019-01-04","Animal Welfare","1","House of Commons","To ask the Leader of the House, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on the allocation of time to debate (a) the matter of and (b) legislative proposals in relation to animal sentience.","false","Biography information for Dr David Drew","Stroud","Dr David Drew","205158"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035125","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-10","<p>The number of doctors who received certificates of completion of training in radiology are shown in the following table.</p><p> </p><p>Number of newly qualified radiologists in England between 2014 and 2018</p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>2014</p></td><td><p>2015</p></td><td><p>2016</p></td><td><p>2017</p></td><td><p>2018</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Radiologist qualifiers</p></td><td><p>176</p></td><td><p>162</p></td><td><p>168</p></td><td><p>171</p></td><td><p>166</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p>Source: Health Education England</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2019-01-10T13:43:06.513Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035125/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035125/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035125/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-04","Radiology","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many newly qualified radiologists there have been in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Siobhain McDonagh","Mitcham and Morden","Siobhain McDonagh","205131"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035126","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-10","<p>NHS England does not allocate funding directly to midwifery services, therefore the information requested is not centrally held. Commissioning decisions are made locally by clinical commissioning groups.</p>","Thurrock","Jackie Doyle-Price",,"2019-01-10T13:48:52.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035126/answer","Biography information for Jackie Doyle-Price","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035126/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035126/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2019-01-04","Maternity Services","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what funding his Department has allocated to NHS midwifery services in each of the last 10 years; and how that funding was spent by those services.","false","Biography information for Siobhain McDonagh","Mitcham and Morden","Siobhain McDonagh","205132"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035127","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-09","<p>Since military operations began, the Global Coalition and its partners in Syria and Iraq have recaptured almost all the territory once held by Daesh, and important advances have been made in recent weeks in the last area of eastern Syria to be occupied by Daesh.</p><p>As the United States has made clear, their announcement does not signal the end of the Coalition or its campaign. Much remains to be done and Daesh will remain a threat even without territory. The UK remains committed to the Coalition and its objective of ensuring Daesh's enduring defeat. We are discussing with the US the implications of their announcement and seeking clarity on their further plans.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2019-01-09T14:29:50.73Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035127/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035127/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035127/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-04","Islamic State: Military Intervention","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what assessment he has made of the effect on (a) Operation Shader and (b) the capacity of UK armed forces to call in airstrikes from the ground of the announcement by the US Administration of the withdrawal of ground troops from Syria.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","205372"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035128","Department for International Development","false","2019-01-09","<p>In common with other government departments and in response to a request from the Cabinet Office, DFID has been considering what support it may be able to offer other government departments in the event of a no deal EU Exit. This contingency planning is specifically for a no deal EU Exit scenario only.</p><p> </p><p>In all scenarios, essential DFID business must continue to ensure that we meet the 0.7% commitment, with impact and value for money. EU exit will not prevent us from continuing the lifesaving humanitarian work that we carry out around the world.</p>","West Worcestershire","Harriett Baldwin",,"2019-01-09T14:23:52.36Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035128/answer","Biography information for Harriett Baldwin","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035128/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035128/answer",,,,,"20","International Development","International Development","2019-01-04","Overseas Aid","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for International Development, what steps she has taken to ensure that the effectiveness of UK ODA will not be affected by reductions in the number of staff in her Department.","false","Biography information for Lloyd Russell-Moyle","Brighton, Kemptown","Lloyd Russell-Moyle","205373"
