"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035133","Ministry of Defence","false","2019-01-15","<p>Between 2012-2017 only one Service Inquiry was conducted, in 2015, where heat illness was specifically found to be a causal or contributory factor following a military exercise.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2019-01-15T15:37:49.063Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035133/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035133/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035133/answer","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1035133/answer/previousversion/95308","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","11","Defence","Defence","2019-01-04","Armed Forces: Death","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, how many Service Inquires conducted after a death during a (a) training exercise and (b) selection event included heat illness as a factor in (i) 2012, (ii) 2013, (iii) 2014, (iv) 2015, (v) 2016 and (vi) 2017.","false","Biography information for Mrs Madeleine Moon","Bridgend","Mrs Madeleine Moon","205219"
