"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029475","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2019-01-10","<p>As part of the Department’s ‘no deal’ European Union exit contingency planning a tender process to procure additional warehouse space for stockpiled medicines, including ambient, refrigerated and controlled drug storage, was undertaken in October 2018.</p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2019-01-10T13:41:56.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029475/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029475/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029475/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-12-20","NHS: Drugs","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what estimate his Department has made of the number of refrigerators purchased for the preservation of medicines as part of contingency planning in the event the UK leaves the EU without a deal up to 20 December 2018.","false","Biography information for Nick Smith","Blaenau Gwent","Nick Smith","204472"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029476","Treasury","false","2019-01-14","<p>HMT organises its records in such a way that does not hold a collection or archive of information on wholly owned government companies.</p><p>The selection of records in the HM Treasury archive is based on its core activities of government economic policy and control of public expenditure that are of cultural and historical value.</p><p> </p><p>The HM Treasury archive collection is available for public viewing via The National Archives (TNA) website.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-01-14T10:39:51.013Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029476/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029476/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029476/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-12-20","Government Controlled Companies","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, where his Department archives information on wholly owned government companies; and whether such information is available for public review.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","204590"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029477","Treasury","false","2019-01-14","<p>We have retained the documents under section 3(4) of the Public Records Act 1958 pending security clearance from relevant Government departments. Once we are satisfied that there are no grounds for retaining the documents, these will be deposited in the National Archives in accordance with the Public Records Act 1958.</p>","Newark","Robert Jenrick",,"2019-01-14T10:41:36.89Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029477/answer","Biography information for Robert Jenrick","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029477/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/1029477/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","Treasury","2018-12-20","International Military Services: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Chancellor of the Exchequer, if he will place a copy of Financial relationships with International Military Services Ltd (IMS) 1981-1984 [T 458/55], currently withheld from the National Archives, in the Library.","false","Biography information for Tulip Siddiq","Hampstead and Kilburn","Tulip Siddiq","204591"
